info.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 31 at 1:36PM CST until February 01 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 10 AM CST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...Very cold wind chills as low as 30 below zero expected. * WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis and Central St. Louis Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Bois Forte Band, Lake Vermilion and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 10 AM CST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
info.instruction: Use caution while traveling outside tonight. Wear the appropriate layers clothing, a hat, and gloves.
